<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-066-658  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 066 658.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>MacWEEK  Jan 16 1990 v4 n2 p3(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Coastal Associates Publishing L.P. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Cube gets high-res scanner. (scanner for NeXT computer) (productannouncement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Farber, Daniel.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   HSD Microcomputer U.S. Inc. (product introduction).andO;Product:   Next (Workstation) (equipment and supplies)HSD Scan-X 1600 (Scanning device) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     ScanningI-O DevicesHigh ResolutionProduct Introduction.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>By Daniel FarberandM;Redwood City, Calif.andP;  -- HSD Microcomputer U.S.andP;  is shipping the firsthigh-resolution scanner for the NeXT Computer System.andP;  The flatbed Scan-X1600 scanner recognizes up to 256 shades of gray and can scan line art at upto 1,600 dpi.andM;The unit's 400-dpi native scan resolution matches the 400-dpi output of theNeXT laser printer.andP;  The $4,995 scanner has 2 Mbytes of RAM and supports TIFFand En-capsulated PostScript file formats.andM;The Scan-X software, which is shipped on a 256-Mbyte optical disc, providesbasic scanning capabilities.andP;  Users can select between 200 and 1,600 dpi forline art and 200, 300 or 400 dpi for gray-scale images.andP;  Multiple frames orportions of an image can be scanned.andM;&quot;We are leaving the image-editing capabilities to other companies,&quot; saidDavid Peter, president of HSD.andP;  &quot;From within Medialogic's Artisan, forexample, you will be able to get direct access to the HSD scanner.andP;  We aremaking an object available to developers that allows programs to directlyaccess the scanner, and we also provide them with IPC (interprocesscommunication) hooks, which allow users to request and send scanned imagesback and forth between applications.&quot;andM;The scanner is available through Businessland outlets.andP;  HSD sells direct toeducation, government and NeXT developers.andM;HSD Microcomputer U.S., a subsidiary of HSD GmbH of Berlin, is at 2000Broadway, Redwood City, Calif.andP;  94063; (415) 367-1797.andO;</TEXT></DOC>